Ing '''miyagapeng pamanisip''' ('''parallel thinking''') metung yang kataya o terminung lelangan na ampong ginamit [[Edward de Bono]].<ref>Edward De Bono, ''Parallel thinking: from Socratic thinking to de Bono thinking'', Viking 1994 ISBN 0-670-85126-4, page x</ref><ref name=frame>David Moseley, Vivienne Baumfield, Julian Elliott, ''Frameworks for thinking: a handbook for teaching and learning'', Cambridge University Press 2005, ISBN 0-521-84831-8, page 135</ref> Lalarawan de ing miyagapeng pamanisip antimong metung a konstruktibung alternatiba king "misasalungat a pamanisip" (''adversarial thinking"), [[dibati]] ampong keraklan ing paralan a yang balu tamung yang pipilinan ning GG3 (Greek gang of three).<ref>Edward De Bono, ''Parallel thinking: from Socratic thinking to de Bono thinking'', Viking 1994
ISBN 0-670-85126-4, page 36–38</ref> Keraklan, ing miyagapeng pamanisip, metung yang lalu pang pamanalkus kareng mas kilalang patalindking a prosesu ning pamanisip (''lateral thinking processes''), at lalung tututuk kareng pamaglakbe  (''focusing even more on explorations'')—ing pamanintun king ''nung nanu ing malyaring maging'' (''what can be'') kesa king ''nung nanu ing atyu'' (''what is'') .

